<br>
   In response to those that say &quot; our role doesn't include being a tank&quot; I'd disagree. We are no doubt the weakest DPS of the melee classes but we get plate armor and defensive abilities. We should have some way to gain agro and serve as an emergency tank like every other plate class and many chain classes. I'm not talking about the ability to replace the role of knights as tanks, merely a tool to peel agro off a caster and hold it for 5-10 seconds until a real tank picks it up. Many mobs in the endgame content are unmezzable, uncharmable, immune to slow, snare, lull, and very MR to boot. This leaves us few options when our spells wont land until the mobs have been debuffed.<br>
<br>
  Some bards say we shouldn't be able to generate agro and that it isn't important. Why shouldn't we? Every other class in the game has to worry about taking agro to some degree except bards. Many classes have tools to reduce agro from just melee damage. We can't even get it when we are actively trying! What is so bad about bards having a way to take agro when needed ? How is that so broken when you consider the agro issues in the game? Please explain agro haters, I really don't understand your logic.<br>
<br>
Muse Sournote<br>
Innoruuk Server <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=santino>santino</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Minstrel</span><br>  Posts: 316<br> <font color=#330000>(7/22/04 7:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19619.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: agro issues</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>We can't even get it when we are actively trying! What is so bad about bards having a way to take agro when needed ? How is that so broken when you consider the agro issues in the game? Please explain agro haters, I really don't understand your logic.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
