<br>
Take rangers for instance. I can tank much better than they can, but they can get aggro very easily. I don't think it should come to the point where people grab a bard over another tank because we bring more to the table. We already have a very specialized role and while I would love taunt I don't feel it is necessary and it would probably be accompanied by other nerfs.<br>
<br>
If we do get it I would prefer it in the form of a song, say a song that gives 500 hate per pulse. This would force us to use up a spell gem and take a song away from our twist for taunting purposes. That is a pretty fair tradeoff if you ask me. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=trilca>Trilca</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://mywebpages.comcast.net/raybo86/avatar/tril%20avatar1.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Minstrel</span><br>  Posts: 150<br> <font color=#330000>(7/23/04 3:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19619.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: agro issues</span><hr size=1> /shrug I found that I got romped on rather handily, MANY times,  the other day in Ik JUST by singing ae mana.. do bards need a way to pull aggro? yes.. sometimes we do.. when i'm kiting a mob and wanna keep it on me and am madly twisting dots at it and running in crazy circles? yes.. but most times? not a chance in heck. :P   <br>
